  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add the chips to the tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crispy – these are your<strong> fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are in the oven, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> smoked paprika</strong> to a bowl and give everything a good mix up then set aside</p><p>Add the <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to a shallow plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>herbed flour mix</strong></p><p>Tip: For a spicier burger, go heavy on the black pepper!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> from the bowl and firmly press each one into the <strong>herbed flour mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>making sure to evenly coat them on both sides – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken</strong> and cook for 8-9 min on each side or until golden brown, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> crispy fried chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1949.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
